&quot;Hello this is from Microsoft.&quot;

&quot;... I think you have the wrong number.&quot;

&quot;Is this Jakob?&quot;

&quot;Okay go on.&quot;

&quot;Yes so we were made aware that some of your files are not updated for security purposes and we would be glad to help you today sir.&quot;

(At this point I knew it was a scam. I&#039;ve heard about this before, plus Indian accent plus Microsoft isn&#039;t going to call you up randomly from this anyways.)

&quot;I... Sure okay.&quot;

&quot;Are you at your computer sir?&quot;

&quot;Yes.&quot;

&quot;Okay turn it on sir.&quot;

&quot;It&#039;s on.&quot;

&quot;Okay so we&#039;re glad to help you. Now look on your keyboard; do you see the Windows key? Should look like the four--&quot;

&quot;Yes.&quot;

&quot;Okay press and hold that down and press R.&quot;

I do, because I know what this does and at this point it&#039;s nothing harmful. It pulls up the run dialogue.

&quot;Okay I need you to type this in. E as in... V as in... No V as in, not.... E as in... N as in... T as in... V as in... W as in... R as in...&quot;

&quot;Okay so E-v-e-n-t-v-w-r?&quot;

&quot;Yes sir. Now press &#039;ok.&#039;&quot;

At this point I knew it was close to getting to the scam part but I couldn&#039;t remember which was which.

&quot;Okay hold on a second.&quot;

&quot;Okay sir.&quot;

&quot;Yeah just hold justtt a second...&quot;

Copy/pasted that into Google&#039;s search engine, of course the first few results were people discussing that alone as a scam where people will call you up and list normal processes as &quot;viruses&quot;.

&quot;Are you there sir?&quot;

&quot;So... I want to thank you for helping me on this... Because sir, I&#039;m glad to educate myself... You see. I&#039;m not stupid. Now I know a lot of people are, but some of us actually know what we&#039;re doing with computers, and aren&#039;t dumb enough to fall for a scam, so you can go f--&quot;

-Click-

Shit made me laugh more than anything.
